From ebb08a00878e242ad79501b0ec1d4f1d0707b7f2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramasamy Kaliappan <rkaliapp@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Oct 2025 21:33:52 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:QSDK:PROTOCOL:hostapd: Clear autorized flag after SA query
 timeout

When an authorized legacy STA entry exists on link 1 and an
unauthorized legacy STA entry exists on link 0 due to roaming,
Later, post sa query timeout when an association request is received
on link 1 from the same MAC address, pruning on the other link is not
triggered because the sta already authorized state.

Fixes the issue by clearing the authorized flag after the SA Query timeout,
ensuring proper handling during the next association request.

Patch-dependency: r58-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-Fix-legacy-station-assoc-failure.patch

Signed-off-by: Ramasamy Kaliappan <rkaliapp@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/ieee802_11.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/ap/ieee802_11.c b/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
index 324bd37218eb..0c6b9897e495 100644
--- a/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
+++ b/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
@@ -6227,6 +6227,7 @@ static void handle_assoc(struct hostapd_data *hapd,
 		 * unprotected frame would be received by the STA that is now
 		 * trying to associate.
 		 */
+		sta->flags &= ~WLAN_STA_AUTHORIZED;
 	}
 
 	/* Make sure that the previously registered inactivity timer will not
-- 
